Executed `cargo test --workspace`.

The publication path keeps guarantees explicit instead of blurring local durability with remote publication:
- `LocalPublicationOutcome` reports `DurabilityMode::Local`
- the active head remains local and unpublished
- manifest generation and published segment ids are surfaced explicitly

The `engine::tests::publication_keeps_durability_and_publication_boundaries_explicit` test verifies that publication leaves the active head local while adding remote references for rolled segments.
